### Error Handling Scenarios (standalone)

### 1) Invalid dependency (expects 400 INVALID_TASK_DEPENDENCY)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

[
  {
    "taskCode": "A",
    "operationName": "Task A",
    "elementName": "Element A",
    "duration": 5,
    "crew": { "name": "Crew A", "assignment": 1 },
    "equipment": [],
    "dependencies": ["NONEXISTENT"]
  }
]

### 2) Circular dependency (expects 400 CIRCULAR_DEPENDENCY)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

[
  {
    "taskCode": "A",
    "operationName": "Task A",
    "elementName": "Element A",
    "duration": 5,
    "crew": { "name": "Crew A", "assignment": 1 },
    "equipment": [],
    "dependencies": ["B"]
  },
  {
    "taskCode": "B",
    "operationName": "Task B",
    "elementName": "Element B",
    "duration": 3,
    "crew": { "name": "Crew B", "assignment": 1 },
    "equipment": [],
    "dependencies": ["A"]
  }
]

### 3) Empty task list (expects 400 INVALID_PARAMETER_VALUE)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

[]